  "response": "The concept of \"credits\" doesn't exist on Quora. Quora is a question-and-answer platform where users can ask questions, provide answers, and engage in discussions. Instead of a credit system, users can receive upvotes or downvotes based on the quality of their contributions. Upvotes can help answers gain more visibility, while downvotes can decrease their prominence. Additionally, users can earn reputation points based on their activity and the reception of their answers.",
